images.title: Carina Nebula
images.description: Young Stars in Early Stages of Formation. The Carina Nebula is one of the largest star-forming regions in space.

images.title: Nearby Galaxy NGC 1365
images.description: NGC 1365 is a barred spiral galaxy located 56 million light-years away in the constellation Fornax.

images.title: Chamaeleon I cloud
images.description: The Chamaeleon I cloud is a star-forming region in the southern hemisphere.

images.title: Stefan’s Quintet
images.description: This compact group of five galaxies is known for dramatic interactions between its members.

images.title: Herbig Haro object 797 (HH 797)
images.description: Herbig Haro objects are small patches of nebulosity associated with newly born stars.

images.title: Herbig Haro object 797 (HH 797) II
images.description: Herbig Haro objects are formed when jets of gas ejected by young stars collide with surrounding gas and dust.
